<subSubSection pageId="23" pageNumber="210" type="diagnosis">
<paragraph blockId="23.[151,1436,1408,1613]" pageId="23" pageNumber="210">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[151,273,1408,1433]" pageId="23" pageNumber="210">Diagnosis.</emphasis>
This is a monotypic group, possibly related to the 
<taxonomicName box="[852,975,1408,1433]" class="Arachnida" family="Gnaphosidae" genus="Berlandina" kingdom="Animalia" order="Araneae" pageId="23" pageNumber="210" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="shnitnikovi">
<emphasis box="[852,975,1408,1433]" italics="true" pageId="23" pageNumber="210">shnitnikovi</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
group. This group can be recognized by (
<number box="[161,173,1445,1469]" pageId="23" pageNumber="210" value="1.0">1</number>
) the large tibial apophysis with the tip bent dorsally, (
<number box="[779,794,1445,1469]" pageId="23" pageNumber="210" value="2.0">2</number>
) seminal duct making a right angle, (
<number box="[1214,1228,1445,1469]" pageId="23" pageNumber="210" value="3.0">3</number>
) the small median apophysis, (
<number box="[285,300,1481,1505]" pageId="23" pageNumber="210" value="4.0">4</number>
) the embolus starting at about 
<number box="[646,695,1481,1505]" pageId="23" pageNumber="210" value="7.3">7.30</number>
–8.00 o’clock, (
<number box="[872,886,1480,1505]" pageId="23" pageNumber="210" value="5.0">5</number>
) the embolus thin and bent at right angle near tip and (
<number box="[207,221,1516,1541]" pageId="23" pageNumber="210" value="5.0">5</number>
) the epigyne with trapezoidal fovea and septum.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection pageId="23" pageNumber="210" type="discussion">
<paragraph blockId="23.[151,1436,1408,1613]" pageId="23" pageNumber="210">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,317,1552,1577]" pageId="23" pageNumber="210">Comment</emphasis>
. According to Ponomarev (personal communication) this species is related to the 
<typeStatus box="[1230,1278,1553,1577]" pageId="23" pageNumber="210">type</typeStatus>
species of the genus and therefore the correct name can be 
<taxonomicName box="[651,747,1588,1613]" class="Arachnida" family="Sparassidae" genus="Berlandia" kingdom="Animalia" order="Araneae" pageId="23" pageNumber="210" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="plumalis">
<emphasis box="[651,747,1588,1613]" italics="true" pageId="23" pageNumber="210">plumalis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
group.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
